createStakerNode().details: Only callable by accounts with STAKER_NODE_CREATOR_ROLE

returns._0: The IStakerNode interface of the newly created staker node
An array of all IStakerNode interfaces

params.nodeId: The ID of the staker node

returns._0: The IStakerNode interface of the staker node

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

returns._0: uint256 The number of staker nodes

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

returns._0: bool True if the caller is the liquid token manager, false otherwise
bool True if the address has the role, false otherwise

initialize((address,address,address,uint.details: This function can only be called once due to the initializer modifier

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `callerConfirmation`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

setMaxNodes(uint256).details: Can only be called by an account with DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE

upgradeStakerNodeImplementation(address).details: Can only be called by an account with DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE

params._implementationContract: Address of the new implementation contract

getNodeById(uint256).notice: Retrieves a staker node by its ID

getStakerNodesCount().notice: Gets the total number of staker nodes

hasLiquidTokenManagerRole(address).notice: Checks if a caller is the liquid token manager

hasStakerNodeDelegatorRole(address).notice: Checks if an address has the STAKER_NODES_DELEGATOR_ROLE

liquidTokenManager().notice: Gets the liquid token manager contract

maxNodes().notice: Gets the maximum number of nodes allowed

setMaxNodes(uint256).notice: Sets the maximum number of staker nodes
